# Coding Standards Guide

## Kotlin Standards

1. Follow Kotlin coding conventions
2. Use Kotlin idioms and best practices
3. Prefer immutable data structures
4. Use coroutines for asynchronous operations
5. Implement proper error handling
6. Use sealed classes for state management
7. Follow SOLID principles

## Compose Guidelines

1. Create reusable composable functions
2. Use proper state management
3. Implement proper theme support
4. Follow Material Design guidelines
5. Optimize recomposition
6. Use proper navigation patterns
7. Implement proper error states
8. Handle configuration changes

## Architecture

1. Implement proper separation of concerns
2. Use repository pattern for data access
3. Implement proper error handling
4. Use proper state management
5. Follow clean architecture principles
6. Implement proper testing

## Testing

1. Write unit tests for business logic
2. Implement UI tests for Compose
3. Use proper test naming conventions
4. Mock external dependencies
5. Test error cases
6. Implement proper test coverage
7. Use proper testing frameworks
8. Follow testing best practices

## Documentation

1. Document public APIs
2. Use KDoc for documentation
3. Include usage examples
4. Document error cases
5. Keep documentation up to date
6. Document configuration options
7. Include migration guides
8. Document breaking changes
